================================================================================
  SECTION 1 — CRITICAL (Fix Immediately)
================================================================================

[x] 1.1  DATABASE CONNECTION LEAK — AnalyticsDashboardService
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure/Services/AnalyticsDashboardService.cs
         Every dashboard method calls db.Database.OpenConnectionAsync() but never
         closes the connection. After ~50-100 dashboard requests the connection
         pool is exhausted and the app deadlocks.
         Fix: Wrap each method in try/finally with connection.CloseAsync(), or
         use `await using` on the connection scope.

[x] 1.2  NEWSLETTER SEND HAS NO TRANSACTION BOUNDARY — NewsletterService
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Core/Services/NewsletterService.cs (lines 157-230)
         Bulk email send spans multiple SaveChangesAsync calls (Email record,
         Batch record, Recipients, then per-recipient updates) with no wrapping
         transaction. If the app crashes mid-send, the database is left
         inconsistent: some emails sent but not recorded, or recipients created
         but delivery status unknown.
         Fix: Wrap the entire send operation in an explicit transaction. Consider
         the Outbox pattern for the external MTA call.

[x] 1.3  EXCESSIVE PER-RECIPIENT SaveChangesAsync — NewsletterService + EmailRepository
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Core/Services/NewsletterService.cs (lines 203-235)
         After sending, each recipient's status is updated with its own
         SaveChangesAsync call. For 500 recipients = 500 DB round-trips (~25s).
         Fix: Batch updates with UpdateRange() and a single SaveChangesAsync,
         or chunk into groups of 100.

[x] 1.4  CREDENTIALS IN VERSION CONTROL — appsettings.Development.json
         Files: src/HowToSoftware.Web/appsettings.Development.json
                src/HowToSoftware.Admin/appsettings.Development.json
         Plain-text database password, Mailgun API key, and SMTP credentials are
         committed. Even for dev configs this is a risk if the repo is public or
         compromised.
         Fix: Move all secrets to user-secrets, environment variables, or a vault.
         Scrub from git history with `git filter-repo`.

[x] 1.5  API KEY EXPOSED IN QUERY STRING — ContentApiKeyHandler
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Web/Authentication/ContentApiKeyHandler.cs
         Content API uses ?key={apiKey} query parameter. Keys leak to server
         logs, browser history, Referer headers, and monitoring dashboards.
         Fix: Migrate to Authorization: Bearer header. Keep ?key= as deprecated
         fallback with a sunset date.

[x] 1.6  TABLE NAME BRACKET INJECTION — TSqlGenerator (Migrator)
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Migrator/TSqlGenerator.cs (~line 350)
         Table names in INSERT statements are wrapped in [] but ] inside the name
         is not escaped. A malicious MySQL dump could inject SQL.
         Fix: Escape ] as ]] in all identifiers, and/or whitelist known Ghost
         table names.


================================================================================
  SECTION 2 — HIGH SEVERITY (Schedule This Sprint)
================================================================================

[x] 2.1  EF CORE PREVIEW PACKAGES IN PRODUCTION
         File: Directory.Packages.props
         EF Core 10.0.0-preview.2.25163.8 and Identity preview packages.
         Preview packages may have breaking changes, security patches may not
         ship to previews, and there is no backward-compat guarantee.
         Fix: Upgrade to stable EF Core 10 when RTM ships, or pin to .NET 9
         stable if production timeline demands it.

[x] 2.2  NO RATE LIMITING ON PUBLIC ENDPOINTS
         Affected endpoints (no rate limiting):
           POST /api/analytics/event — abuse → DB exhaustion
           POST /api/donations/checkout — abuse → Stripe session flooding
           POST /api/member/magic-link — abuse → email spam
           POST /api/member/signup — abuse → mass fake accounts
           POST /api/recommendations/{id}/click
           POST /api/recommendations/{id}/subscribe
           GET  /api/content/* (per-key throttle missing)
         Fix: Implement ASP.NET Core 10 built-in rate limiting middleware.
         Configure per-IP and per-key sliding windows.

[x] 2.3  NO EMAIL VERIFICATION ON SIGNUP — MemberAuthController
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Web/Controllers/MemberAuthController.cs (~line 97)
         New members are auto-authenticated without verifying their email.
         Enables account takeover, newsletter spam, and mass fake registrations.
         Fix: Send verification email; only create session after token click.

[x] 2.4  POTENTIAL XSS IN CONTENT RENDERING
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Web/Pages/Post.cshtml.cs (~line 40)
         post.Html is rendered directly. If content contains malicious JS
         (e.g. from a compromised admin editor or database injection), it
         executes in visitor browsers.
         Fix: Sanitize HTML before rendering. Use HtmlSanitizer NuGet package
         or a CSP nonce strategy.

[x] 2.5  MISSING INPUT VALIDATION — DonationsController
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Web/Controllers/DonationsController.cs
         No maximum donation amount limit. SuccessUrl and CancelUrl not
         validated — potential open-redirect via Stripe checkout.
         Fix: Add [Range] attribute on amount, validate URLs are same-origin.

[x] 2.6  WEBMENTION CONTENT NOT SANITIZED
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Web/Controllers/WebmentionController.cs
         External source/target URLs accepted with minimal validation (only
         empty-string check). Fetched metadata stored without HTML sanitization.
         Fix: Validate URL format, verify source references target, sanitize
         all fetched metadata before storage.

[x] 2.7  ADMIN BLAZOR AUTHORIZATION TOO BROAD
         Files: src/HowToSoftware.Admin/Components/Pages/*
         Several admin pages grant access to Editor/Author/Contributor roles
         that should be restricted to Owner/Administrator only:
           - Members CSV export
           - Staff role management
           - System settings
         Fix: Audit each page's [Authorize] attribute. Apply least-privilege.

[ ] 2.8  SIGNALR HUB — NO PER-METHOD RATE LIMIT OR INPUT VALIDATION
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Admin/Hubs/AnalyticsHub.cs
         Class-level authorization exists but individual methods don't validate
         date range bounds or rate-limit requests.
         Fix: Add date range ceiling (365 days), per-user request throttle,
         and access logging.

[ ] 2.9  MISSING CSRF VALIDATION IN BLAZOR FORMS
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Admin/Program.cs (line 75)
         app.UseAntiforgery() is called but Blazor interactive components
         may not embed/validate tokens consistently.
         Fix: Verify all EditForm components include <AntiforgeryToken />
         and use [SupplyParameterFromForm].

[ ] 2.10 WEBHOOK DISPATCH SILENTLY DROPS EVENTS
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure/Services/WebhookDispatchService.cs
         Bounded channel (1000 items) uses DropOldest policy. If queue fills,
         webhook events are silently lost with no notification.
         Fix: Switch to BoundedChannelFullMode.Wait, or log + alert when queue
         reaches 80% capacity.


================================================================================
  SECTION 3 — MEDIUM SEVERITY (Next Sprint)
================================================================================

[ ] 3.1  OPEN REDIRECT POTENTIAL — MagicLinkRequest.RedirectUrl
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Web/Controllers/MemberAuthController.cs
         RedirectUrl field in magic-link request not validated.
         Fix: Whitelist allowed paths, reject external URLs with Url.IsLocalUrl().

[ ] 3.2  ADMIN SESSION TIMEOUT TOO LONG (14 days sliding)
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Admin/Program.cs (line 29)
         Admin sessions slide for 14 days — effectively infinite with activity.
         Fix: Reduce to 2 hours, disable sliding expiration.

[ ] 3.3  MEMBER SESSION TIMEOUT TOO LONG (30 days sliding)
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Web/Program.cs (~line 30)
         Fix: Reduce to 7 days, consider disabling sliding.

[ ] 3.4  NO AUDIT LOGGING FOR PRIVILEGED OPERATIONS
         Missing audit trail for: API key creation/rotation, staff role changes,
         content deletion, data exports, settings modification.
         Fix: Create an append-only audit log table. Log user, operation,
         timestamp, IP, resource, and result.

[ ] 3.5  SETTINGS SERVICE CACHE RACE CONDITION
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Core/Services/SettingsService.cs (lines 57-67)
         Multiple threads can pass the null check, all fetch from the repo,
         and last one wins. Not fatal but wastes DB queries on cold start.
         Fix: Use SemaphoreSlim for async-safe cache population.

[ ] 3.6  MEMBER SIGNUP RETURNS NULL INSTEAD OF RESULT TYPE
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Core/Services/MemberService.cs (lines 60-75)
         SignupAsync returns null for duplicate email — caller can't distinguish
         "already exists" from "unexpected error."
         Fix: Return a result type with status codes, or throw a typed exception.

[ ] 3.7  AUTOMATED EMAIL SERVICE — SILENT FAILURES
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Core/Services/AutomatedEmailService.cs (lines 31-58)
         Multiple early-return paths (email not found, inactive, suppressed) all
         return void with only log messages. Callers never know if send happened.
         Fix: Return an enum status (Sent, SkippedInactive, SkippedSuppressed,
         NotFound).

[ ] 3.8  HARD-CODED IP ADDRESSES
         Files: deploy/caddy/Caddyfile.edge (reverse_proxy targets)
                src/HowToSoftware.Web/Program.cs (KnownProxies)
                deploy.ps1 ($Target)
         Fix: Move to configuration or DNS names. At minimum, read from
         environment variables.

[ ] 3.9  MAGIC LINK SERVICE — NO RETRY ON EMAIL FAILURE
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure/Services/MagicLinkService.cs
         If the email send fails, the magic link token is consumed but never
         delivered. No retry logic, no notification to user.
         Fix: Add retry with exponential backoff (Polly) or re-queue on failure.

[ ] 3.10 STRIPE SERVICE — NO ROLLBACK ON STRIPE API FAILURE
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure/Services/StripeService.cs (~line 90)
         If Stripe API call fails after the local DB insert, records become
         inconsistent.
         Fix: Use Stripe idempotency keys and wrap in transaction with
         compensation logic.

[ ] 3.11 TLS SKIP VERIFY ON PANEL REVERSE PROXY
         File: deploy/caddy/Caddyfile.edge
         panel.howto.software uses tls_insecure_skip_verify = true.
         Fix: Obtain proper internal certificate or configure self-signed chain.

[ ] 3.12 NO CORS CONFIGURATION
         Content API endpoints (/api/content/*) have no explicit CORS headers.
         Third-party JavaScript clients cannot consume the API.
         Fix: Add CORS policy for Content API with allowed origins config.


