  SECTION 4 — LOW SEVERITY / IMPROVEMENTS
================================================================================

[x] 4.1  COMPILER WARNING — CS8603 null reference return
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Migrator/MySqlDumpParser.cs (line 144)
         Fix: Add null-forgiving operator or explicit null check.

[ ] 4.2  REMOVE PreserveCompilationContext FROM INFRASTRUCTURE
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure.csproj
         Not needed unless runtime compilation is used. Adds output size.

[ ] 4.3  CSP ALLOWS unsafe-inline FOR SCRIPTS AND STYLES
         File: deploy/caddy/Caddyfile.edge
         Fix: Implement nonce-based CSP, or audit all inline scripts/styles.

[ ] 4.4  DOCKER IMAGES USE TAGS, NOT DIGESTS
         Files: deploy/Dockerfile.web, deploy/Dockerfile.admin
         Using mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:10.0 without @sha256 digest.
         Fix: Pin to SHA256 digests for reproducible builds.

[ ] 4.5  DEPLOY SCRIPT — SPECIAL CHARS IN PASSWORDS BREAK .env
         File: deploy.ps1
         echo '$line' > .env is fragile with $, ", and ' in passwords.
         Fix: Generate .env locally and scp it, or use here-document.

[ ] 4.6  DEPLOY SCRIPT — NO ROLLBACK MECHANISM
         File: deploy.ps1
         If deployment fails mid-way, no automated rollback to previous images.
         Fix: Tag previous images before deploy, add rollback command.

[ ] 4.7  DEPLOY SCRIPT — NO POST-DEPLOY HEALTH CHECK
         File: deploy.ps1
         Script completes after docker compose up without waiting for health.
         Fix: Poll /health endpoint after deploy, fail if unhealthy.

[ ] 4.8  MISSING security.txt
         No /.well-known/security.txt for responsible disclosure.
         Fix: Add security contact file to wwwroot.

[ ] 4.9  INCONSISTENT HTTP STATUS CODES ACROSS CONTROLLERS
         Some endpoints return 400 for validation errors, others 422.
         Different error response formats across controllers.
         Fix: Standardize on Ghost-compatible error envelope for all APIs.

[ ] 4.10 NO STRUCTURED LOGGING (Serilog)
         BUILD.md Phase 12.5 marks this incomplete. Only default console logging.
         Fix: Add Serilog with console + file sinks. Add request correlation IDs.

[ ] 4.11 NO OBSERVABILITY STACK (OpenTelemetry)
         No distributed tracing, no metrics export.
         Fix: Add OpenTelemetry packages, configure traces/metrics export.

[ ] 4.12 NO RESILIENCE POLICIES (Polly)
         External integrations (Mailgun, Stripe, webhooks) have no retry logic.
         Fix: Add Polly retry/circuit-breaker for all external HTTP calls.

[ ] 4.13 REPOSITORY — PostsWithIncludes() OVER-FETCHES
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure/Data/Repositories/PostRepository.cs
         Every query loads 4 nested includes. For listing endpoints that only
         need Title/Slug, this wastes DB resources.
         Fix: Create specialized query methods (PostsWithTagsOnly, etc.).

[ ] 4.14 REPOSITORY — GetRelatedPostsAsync USES TWO QUERIES
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure/Data/Repositories/PostRepository.cs
         Gets tag IDs first, then filters posts. Can be single subquery.

[ ] 4.15 MEMBER SEARCH — String.Contains() NOT INDEXED
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Infrastructure/Data/Repositories/MemberRepository.cs
         Use EF.Functions.Like() for index-compatible LIKE queries.

[ ] 4.16 IMAGEMIGRATOR — SYMLINK PATH TRAVERSAL
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Migrator/ImageMigrator.cs (~lines 50-60)
         If Ghost content/images contains symlinks pointing outside the dir,
         files could be copied from unintended locations.
         Fix: Validate destination path stays within target directory.

[ ] 4.17 SQLEXECUTOR — PII LEAKAGE IN ERROR MESSAGES
         File: src/HowToSoftware.Migrator/SqlExecutor.cs (~line 35)
         Batch preview (200 chars) shown on error may contain user emails/data.
         Fix: Sanitize or omit batch preview in error output.

[ ] 4.18 NO EXTERNAL HTTP CALL TIMEOUTS
         Webmention URL fetches and other external calls may not have explicit
         timeouts configured, risking resource exhaustion.
         Fix: Set HttpClient.Timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(10) for all
         external-facing HttpClient instances.


